  "body": "### Description\r\nIn REST APIs like `/validator/attestation` the `aggregation_bitlist` field should be serialised as a variable length SSZ list. We're currently serialising just as a byte array.\r\n\r\n>Paul Hauner, [25 Mar 2020 at 4:51:29 pm]:\r\n> Oh yes this is the length bit of a variable length ssz \"bitlist\"\r\n> \r\n> https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/v0.11.0/ssz/simple-serialize.md#bitlistn\r\n> \r\n> > An additional 1 bit is added to the end, at index e where e is the length of the bitlist (not the limit), so that the length in bits will also be known.\r\n\r\nCurrently we're just serialising as a plain byte array without the SSZ encoding.  We should check any other fields which include binary data to ensure they are also SSZ encoded (In Lighthouse responses anything that's an `0x` kind of value is SSZ encoded).",
